00:02:56.436 --> 00:02:58.556
questioned basic assumptions

00:02:58.916 --> 00:03:00.436
that we all have taken for

00:03:00.436 --> 00:03:00.926
granted.

00:03:01.796 --> 00:03:03.276
They questioned the assumption

00:03:03.336 --> 00:03:05.016
that driving controls required

00:03:05.016 --> 00:03:07.476
acceleration, braking and

00:03:07.476 --> 00:03:07.786
turning.

00:03:08.576 --> 00:03:10.126
So they started completely from

00:03:10.126 --> 00:03:10.626
scratch.

00:03:11.836 --> 00:03:13.896
This led to an exciting idea.

00:03:14.996 --> 00:03:16.526
After being challenged to figure

00:03:16.526 --> 00:03:18.026
out a simplified and more

00:03:18.026 --> 00:03:19.546
accessible control scheme for

00:03:19.546 --> 00:03:21.706
iOS, the developer tried this

00:03:21.706 --> 00:03:23.856
crazy idea that moves the main

00:03:23.856 --> 00:03:25.886
controls away from acceleration

00:03:25.886 --> 00:03:28.376
and braking to nitro and drift

00:03:28.376 --> 00:03:28.856
actions.

00:03:29.916 --> 00:03:31.326
They quickly realized there was

00:03:31.326 --> 00:03:32.716
something special there because

00:03:32.716 --> 00:03:34.376
it helped players get into the

00:03:34.376 --> 00:03:36.446
fun so much faster.

00:03:37.336 --> 00:03:38.566
But they were not done shaking

00:03:38.566 --> 00:03:39.116
things up yet.

00:03:40.156 --> 00:03:42.206
Asphalt 9 knew that traditional

00:03:42.206 --> 00:03:44.486
turning as a player control was

00:03:44.486 --> 00:03:47.236
very prone to player error.

00:03:47.656 --> 00:03:50.086
So after rounds of testing and

00:03:50.086 --> 00:03:52.076
feedback, they replaced

00:03:52.076 --> 00:03:53.966
traditional path -- excuse me,

00:03:53.966 --> 00:03:56.146
they replaced turning with path

00:03:56.456 --> 00:03:58.226
and item selection through swipe

00:03:58.226 --> 00:03:58.716
gestures.

00:03:59.576 --> 00:04:01.246
And this made people less

00:04:01.376 --> 00:04:03.306
frustrated, because it helped

00:04:03.306 --> 00:04:04.556
people focus on learning the

00:04:04.556 --> 00:04:06.536
very elaborate tracks and play

00:04:06.596 --> 00:04:07.476
more strategically.

00:04:09.126 --> 00:04:10.756
So TouchDrive has now become the

00:04:10.756 --> 00:04:12.386
default control scheme for

00:04:12.386 --> 00:04:14.646
strategic racing, fine-tuning

00:04:14.816 --> 00:04:15.826
and level recon.

00:04:16.495 --> 00:04:18.106
Now full manual controls are a

00:04:18.106 --> 00:04:19.596
matter of surgical precision and

00:04:19.596 --> 00:04:20.776
are still available.

00:04:21.326 --> 00:04:23.506
But what I love is that this

00:04:23.556 --> 00:04:25.526
developer took an informed risk.

00:04:26.186 --> 00:04:28.466
After iterating, testing and

00:04:28.466 --> 00:04:30.496
getting feedback, the design

00:04:30.496 --> 00:04:32.336
decision to diverge from

00:04:32.336 --> 00:04:34.716
traditional driving controls has

00:04:34.716 --> 00:04:36.506
allowed for an entirely new

00:04:36.506 --> 00:04:37.966
experience to emerge.

00:04:38.756 --> 00:04:40.596
And the innovation of TouchDrive

00:04:40.846 --> 00:04:42.856
has revealed an entirely new way

00:04:42.856 --> 00:04:43.846
to play the game.

